PKGMK.NOSTRIP(5)

# NAME

pkgmk.nostrip - list of files excluded from stripping by pkgmk

# SYNOPSIS

*.nostrip*

# DESCRIPTION

The _.nostrip_ file lists path or patterns of files that *pkgmk*(8)
must _not_ strip of debug symbols.

By default, *pkgmk*(8) strips binaries and shared libraries using
*strip*(1) to reduce package size.
The _.nostrip_ file overrides this behavior for files where symbols
must be preserved, e.g., for debugging or tool compatibility.

# FILE FORMAT

Each line contains a single path or pattern relative to the package
root.
Blank lines and lines starting with '*#*' are ignored.

Patterns are interpreted as basic regular expressions, as understood
by *grep*(1).
Contributors should note that these are BREs (Basic Regular
Expressions), not extended forms.

# FILES

_.nostrip_
	Manifest file in package source directory; lists files
	excluded from stripping.

# EXAMPLES

Sample _.nostrip_ entries:

```
# Exclude a specific binary
usr/bin/debug-binary

# Exclude a shared library
usr/lib/libunistripped.so

# Exclude a directory
usr/lib/debug-tools/

# Exclude dotfiles (note the escaped dot)
^\\..*

# Exclude everything
.*
```

# SEE ALSO

*pkgmk*(8),
*pkgmk.conf*(5),
*pkgmk.Pkgfile*(5),
